1 A BILL for an Act to provide for a performance audit of the department of commerce.
2 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
3 SECTION 1. PERFORMANCE AUDIT - DEPARTMENT OF COMMERCE. The legislative
4 management shall contract with an out-of-state and independent third party for the completion
5 of a performance audit of the department of commerce for the biennium beginning July 1, 2025,
6 and ending June 30, 2027. The chairman of the legislative management shall arrange for the
7 audit and by August 30, 2026, receive the audit report. The performance audit must address the
8 economy, efficiency, and effectiveness of the department of commerce relative to industry best
9 practices criteria for the years 2020 to 2024 by examining internal processes, controls, and
10 results to identify areas for improvement and provide recommendations for corrective actions.
